This is a Demo for closely Understanding the App-Of-Apps Patern in ArgoCD, to implement for VG-Industrials
As VG-Industrials have 3 sub-projects

1. accounts-online
2. erp
3. reseller

But for the demo we will take reference of an Artical published by CNCF [Cloud Native Computing Foundation]
    Link - https://www.cncf.io/blog/2025/10/07/managing-kubernetes-workloads-using-the-app-of-apps-pattern-in-argocd-2/

Flow -

ArgoCD Installation, Steps to Install ArgoCD
1. kubectl create namespace argocd
2. kubectl apply -n argocd -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj/argo-cd/stable/manifests/install.yaml

## Objects Created when ArgoCD Installed

### CRD - Custom Resource Definations
1. customresourcedefinition.apiextensions.k8s.io/applications.argoproj.io created
    *  Represents an Argo CD Application
    *  This is the core GitOps object

2. customresourcedefinition.apiextensions.k8s.io/applicationsets.argoproj.io created
    * Used by ApplicationSet controller
    * Dynamically generates Applications (useful for monorepos, multi-env)

3. customresourcedefinition.apiextensions.k8s.io/applicationsets.argoproj.io created
    * Used for RBAC, repo whitelisting, namespace restrictions

### Service Accounts (Identity for Pods)
| ServiceAccount                     | Purpose                |
| ---------------------------------- | ---------------------- |
| `argocd-application-controller`    | Syncs Git → Cluster    |
| `argocd-applicationset-controller` | Generates Applications |
| `argocd-server`                    | API + UI               |
| `argocd-repo-server`               | Git repo access        |
| `argocd-dex-server`                | SSO / OIDC             |
| `argocd-redis`                     | Cache                  |
| `argocd-notifications-controller`  | Slack / Teams / Email  |

### RBAC Objects (Permissions)
| `role.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-application-controller created`                  |
| `role.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-applicationset-controller created`               |
| `role.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-dex-server created`                              |
| `role.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-notifications-controller created`                |
| `role.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-redis created`                                   |
| `role.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-server created`                                  |
| `clusterrole.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-application-controller created`           |
| `clusterrole.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-applicationset-controller created`        |
| `clusterrole.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-server created`                           |
| `rolebinding.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-application-controller created`           |
| `rolebinding.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-applicationset-controller created`        |
| `rolebinding.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-dex-server created`                       |
| `rolebinding.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-notifications-controller created`         |
| `rolebinding.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-redis created`                            |
| `rolebinding.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-server created`                           |
| `clusterrolebinding.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-application-controller created`    |
| `clusterrolebinding.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-applicationset-controller created` |
| `clusterrolebinding.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/argocd-server created`                    |

#### Key ones:

`argocd-application-controller`
`argocd-server`
`argocd-applicationset-controller`


### ConfigMaps (Configuration)
1. `argocd-cm`
    * Repo credentials
    * OIDC config
    * UI settings

2. `argocd-rbac-cm`
    * Argo CD RBAC rules
    * argocd-cmd-params-cm
    * Server flags (TLS, ports, insecure)

3. `argocd-notifications-cm`
    * Notification templates
    * argocd-ssh-known-hosts-cm
    * SSH trust for Git repos

### Secrets
1. `argocd-secret`
    * Admin password hash
    * JWT signing key

2. `argocd-notifications-secret`
    * Webhook tokens
    * Slack / Teams credentials

## Folder Structure
```
.
├── app-of-app.yaml
├── apps
│   ├── cert-manager.yaml
│   └── nginx-ingress.yaml
└── charts
    ├── cert-manager
    │   ├── Chart.yaml
    │   ├── templates
    │   └── vaules.yaml
    └── nginx-ingress
        ├── Chart.yaml
        ├── templates
        └── vaules.yaml
```